<HEADLINE>
FT  30 JAN 93 / Property: Listed building legislation
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MY ARTICLE on January 9 mistakenly reported that Simmons &amp; Simmons and
Jackson-Stops says in its Guide to the Legislation Relating to Listed
Buildings that the law requires such buildings to be maintained.
Owners may, however, be served repair notices or a compulsory purchase order
if the building is becoming derelict. After a fire, there is no explicit
obligation to rebuild, but restoration work would usually require consent.
