<HEADLINE>
FT  29 JAN 93 / British Alcan renews coal supply arrangements
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRIS TIGHE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BRITISH ALCAN, the aluminium smelter based in north-east England and British
Coal's largest manufacturing customer, has renewed supply arrangements for
1.2m tonnes of coal a year from Ellington colliery, Northumberland, Chris
Tighe writes.
British Coal, which sells about 6m tonnes a year in the industrial market,
has also announced further orders worth Pounds 40m from industrial companies
for almost 1m tonnes of deep-mined and opencast coal. They include an order
for 500,000 tonnes over three years from Fife-based papermaker Tullis
Russell, a new customer. There is also a new contract from Scottish Power
for 200,000 tonnes.
Ellington, which employs 1,600 people, is the only one of the north-east's
five remaining collieries not earmarked for closure in the October 1992 list
of 31 pits. It was ranked bottom, however, among the remaining 19
collieries.
</TEXT>
