<HEADLINE>
FT  29 JAN 93 / Companies win over rental VAT
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
GRANADA, the leisure, television and computer services group, and Thorn EMI,
the electronics group, yesterday won a joint appeal at a Customs and Excise
tribunal that they will not be required to pay value added tax on insurance
premiums for rental equipment.
The two companies had made no provisions in their accounts because they
believed they were confident of winning, but an adverse ruling would have
cost them more than Pounds 50m.
Stock Exchange, Page 34
