<HEADLINE>
FT  29 JAN 93 / Customs relief on single market
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW JACK
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
IMPLEMENTATION of the single European market is moving smoothly for most UK
businesses, with most difficulties occurring in other EC states, the Customs
and Excise Department said yesterday, Andrew Jack writes.
Mr Mike Rickwood, head of the department's single market unit, said: 'Most
traffic is moving reasonably freely and a lot better than we had feared.'
Companies and professional advisers were reporting that the transition had
been largely effective, but officials admitted there that were still some
problems with the new regime on the Continent, including long delays for
excise goods at the Italian border.
