</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE M0 measure of money supply has risen above its Treasury target range,
indicating some inflationary pressures, according to estimates based on Bank
of England figures published yesterday.
M0, which comprises mainly notes and coins, rose in the four weeks to
yesterday by an estimated seasonally adjusted 4.2 per cent from the
equivalent period last year.
