<HEADLINE>
FT  29 JAN 93 / International Company News: Bank of Boston slips to Dollars
73.6m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALAN FRIEDMAN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BANK of Boston, a leading New England bank, yesterday reported
fourth-quarter net profits of Dollars 73.6m, or 75 cents a share, down from
Dollars 93.5m, or Dollars 1.15, a year ago.
The bank stressed, however, that the level of its bad debt provisions had
declined last year, in the fourth quarter to Dollars 10m from Dollars 78m a
year before. The net profit level would have been just Dollars 56.6m in the
quarter had it not been for a tax credit.
For the whole of 1992, Bank of Boston's net income was Dollars 263.1m, or
Dollars 2.84 a share, a substantial recovery when compared with a loss of
Dollars 26.6m, or 53 cents, in 1991.
The 1992 result was helped by Dollars 71m of tax credits carried forward
from prior years.
On Wall Street, the bank's share price closed Dollars  3/8 higher at Dollars
26 1/8 .
