FT  29 JAN 93 / Arts: Fischer-Dieskau retires
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW CLARK
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Dietrich Fischer-Dieskau has announced his immediate retirement from the
concert platform, writes Andrew Clark. The German baritone, who is 67, gave
no reason for his decision, but said he would continue to give
masterclasses. His last performance was at a gala concert at the Bavarian
State Opera in Munich on New Year's Eve.
